reviews.text: Great specialized science and relevant history. Certainly worth a visit, not very hands-on for younger kids. If cold war nuclear history really interests you, follow up with a visit the the National Nuclear Museum in Albuquerque (pretty much all weapons related).

This is a great museum and it is worth to see. You can spend few hours there and see history of atomic bomb development, nuclear testing and more. Although I was there some time ago (in 2011) my memories are still fresh.
Free and science cool! Their 15 minute movies were informative.

What a wonderful place to visit, but with such a dark history! 
The Bradbury Science Museum is dedicated to all things atomic bomb related in the secretive town of Los Alamos. 
Everything from details of how the area was decided upon to letters from Einstein to Roosevelt, on the dangers of atomic power, to mockups of the Little Boy and Fat Man bombs. 
It’s incredibly interesting and quite daunting too. Admission is free 😬
Highly recommended 👍🏼👍🏼
its fun but the nukes don't go off

It is a small tastefully decorated gift shop/gallery. Very interesting pieces, well conceived and artfully presented. The care taker was very knowledgeable of the art scene, BUT, it seemed very isolated to LA county.

The Fuller Lodge Art Center is the center of the diverse community of talented artists and art teachers. The Lodge boasts a large annual art fair that usually has live music. The Lodge has connections with a diverse community of talented teachers of art and instruments and voice. The lodge hosts several non-advertised concert's put on by musical students and their teachers.
Great local gallery with creative exhibits. Great for kids classes as well as adult art classes! Friendly staff!
Such a beautiful and historic space. We have attended many performances, winter farmers markets, and dances here. We also rented it out for our wedding reception, and it was perfect.

Step into the past with a walk around beautiful Fuller Lodge! Has great performances of music and other things. Offers a nice lawn for yoga and weddings, also for photo ops. Very romantic date location, with benches to sit in.

The food is always very good. I seem to usually end up there when they're closed so I wish they had longer hours. The staff is nice and attentive and the restaurant is clean. I've never had any issues with any good except their eggs are less cooked than we like so we order accordingly..
Top of the line customer service delivered with a smile.  Food it also tops. Highly recommended.

Viola's has been a family go to for a long time.  One serious plus for my family is they have vegitarian red sauce (medium heat).  It is very popular in town so getting there early for lunch is recommended. It gets 4 stars as the interior needs an update. If you are going for spicy this is not the place.
Delious food, great prices & best friendly restaurant. Best ever, been going to Viola's since it was at Zia co
The food was amazing you can tell right of the bat they don’t freeze meat. And the customer service is great.

They have ok tacos, better burritos, and the best burgers there is in the small town of Los Alamos. Dude, I got mine with guacamole, green chili, and nothing off it. It. Was. AMAZING! The service was great, nothing bad. PLEASE go here and order something for yourself or your family because it will be a treat.
Fresh ingredients rich with flavor is a good combo.  Hot food made to order that exceeded my already high expectation.
Good food, good portions, decent price.  Pleasant folks working there too.

Simple foods in a casual place, conveniently located.  I only had a bunch of tamales, I was a happy camper.    :)   Prices aren't "cheap", but it's affordable.  I made notes in my travel guides and recommended it to a few people.

Meh. Ordered sirloin tacos and expected more out of them than the teeny things we got. They were edible and all, but not something I'd stop in for again. They were kind of bland. Took a really long time to get our orders out, not sure exactly how long but while I was waiting, I was able to call both my mom and mother-in-law (you can guess how long each of those calls took...) The atmosphere was tired and it was pretty cold in there.

The food is mediocre at best and is terribly overpriced. The only reason they survive is because they are located directly across the street from the Bandelier National Monument Visitor Center. 

Don't waste your time and money.
Good food, good service, but expect to pay $16 for an $8 meal.
Good food, fun time and gorgeous bartender
No longer the bandolier. No bar.
Super nachos ftw!
Love the food here. The best tasting Chinese food I have tasted. The people that work there are so friendly and are always smiling. Keep up the good work !
Outstanding location for delicious chinese food. Visited Sat afternoon. I will be back with my coworkers. Bring your appetite because portions are filling.

This is our go to place for Chinese food.  They even know us by what we order. We think that this place makes some of the best Chinese food for your run of the mill commercial Chinese joints. 
Very pleasant to deal with. Give them a try you will like it.
Quick, consistent, excellent service with a smile. Love them.
Absolutely wonderful food. Quick and fresh. Nothing was reheated or cold. Great portions.

Picked up some take out. I had the Mongolian Beef with steamed rice and hot & sour soup. The soup was delicious and on the spicy side. Rice was nice and fluffy and I asked for a little cup of the “red sweet/sour sauce” as I like to put it on the rice. They were happy to accommodate my request.
The Mongolian Beef was outstanding! It was still piping hot when I opened the carton at home. The meat was tender and full of flavor. Best I’ve had in town. Will definitely order from them again.

I have a very mixed opinion of this place. Im giving three stars only because the food is always great, fresh, etc which is why I keep going back. HOWEVER, the service in house is subpar. Staff always seems frustrated that you are there and it takes FOREVER to get your food. So only go if you are not in a hurry to be anywhere soon. As far as calling in, good luck. That’s hit or miss. Some days I can get an answer and other days I never am able to get anyone to pick up the phone, and yes- I am calling during their funky business hours. Also, if you call in, still expect it to take at least 30 minutes or more for your food to be ready to be picked up.
Food not to bad.
We love this place. Been following that s business for over 20 years.
Nice Thai food, and inexpensive.

Shelley the receptionist is extraordinary in her job as I witnessed her handle a very agrressive person with the highest standard of professionalism I have seen. Customer service is #1 and Dr. Shin should be proud of such a great person. Randie in Optical is outstanding in helping pick a frame suitable to my face and informed me of every single step in the process. I had a prescription change and Randie immediately called the lab and got everything well organized then called me. Dr Shin has a great Optical Shop with Randie being well versed in the entire process. Well done on all levels, go there for the highest level of professionalism and courtesy. Either an office has that or not and Dr. Shins office has it. Well done

she 's quite rude to Asian and colored people. we tried to get contact lenses, her instructions were completely unclear. in the test, she used her finger to poke my eye directly.
we are quite new here,  and English is not our first language, she often ignore us on purpose.  she would talk to her front desk, other coworkers for some thing trivial instead of answering our questions.
Completely disrespectful, treated us like animals. will never try her again.
She used my email given to her for medical purposes to push her political agenda. Not cool. Done with her.

I went for a check up, all seemed to go well.  Paid my co-pay, and left.  After a few minutes, I was down the hill already, I receive a phone call from the receptionist saying, "Dr. Shin was not done, you need to come back"!!  Really???  Then later, I go back to the office, on a Friday (drive 62 miles) to pick up my RX, receptionist says Dr Shin is really busy, but she will have her email to me before 5pm that day.  I told receptionist I needed it for Saturday, because I had a 2 for 1 coupon at Stanton Optical in Santa Fe.!!! I called and left a message, at 4:30, to say I had not received it yet.  Well, I never got it until sometime Sunday afternoon!!  My coupon had expired, I had to cancel my appointment with Stanton!!!  I wrote Dr. Shin directly, no reply whatsoever!!  Receptionist is rude and unprofessional, almost felt like she didn't like hispanics, and didn't want to deal with me!!   I will find another optometrist.  I'm being kind by rating a 2 star, service was horrible!!

Dr. Shin is the BEST.  She always takes her time with me and I get the best prescription.  I believe that the MacuHealth supplements she recommended have increased my night vision.  I would recommend Dr. Shin to anyone.
Good food. The green chili is really freaking spicy! I had to take most of mine off in order to eat my burrito. Good food though
Fast friendly service. A little pricey for the working man, but good.

I changed my rating from 5 to 1. It use to have great burritos and coffee. They have been down hill for a while. Their "Steak grande" burrito should be call "rice grande" steak poquito burrito. All rice, no steak. Today, half o burrito didn't have any meat

Great place to get lunch and breakfast foods. Quick service. Great breakfast burritos and they had IBC root beer as well. The most deceiving part is that it looks like it inside the lab and it’s inside the public part of the lab.

Once you order at the counter food is brought out pretty quickly. However, sometimes the line is ridiculously long. Avoid peak lunch rush and especially if the summer students are around. The food is on par for the town. It is very convenient for the Lab staff in walking distance. parking can be very tough at Ta-3 though. The breakfast burritos are pretty good.

The food here is spectacular, and the owner is a first-rate human being.  I love their gyros, but if you're not a fan of lamb or chicken, try the Philly cheese steak gyro -- fantastic!
The only negative is that they need more servers, so when they get busy, the service degrades (as one would expect).   They also have trouble getting my order right; it comes out wrong almost every time, though it is admittedly a highly customized order.
Despite those minor inconveniences, we love coming here, and we do so as often as we can.  Highly recommended!

This is some of the worst service I’ve ever recieved. Not only did the waiters/waitresses have no idea how to explain the menu, the wait was awful and we ended up having to hand-deliver our payment to the kitchen because we waited for over 15 minutes (last customers there) and nobody came to pick it up. My Gyro was alright, my friend’s Beef Marga was slightly above average. The saving graces here were the delicious Turkish coffee and side salad that came with my gyro lol.
One of the few places in town to get ethnic food. Casual dining serving gyros, lamb, falafel, hummus, dolmas, pitas, etc.
Food was good, service quick, though the place could use some more decoration.

The food can be hit or miss in quality.  I live the plate that is a combination of hummus and other things, (can't remember the name ).  The ambiance leaves a lot to be desired.  But it is Mediterranean food in Los Alamos,  and I'm glad they're there.
